Enum SoundEffect

java.lang.Object
  java.lang.Enum<SoundEffect>
      SoundEffect
All Implemented Interfaces:
java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Comparable<SoundEffect>
public enum SoundEffect
extends java.lang.Enum<SoundEffect>

This enum encapsulates all the sound effects of a game, so as to separate the sound playing codes from the game codes.
1. Define all your sound effect names and the associated wave file.
2. To play a specific sound, simply invoke SoundEffect.SOUND_NAME.play().
3. You might optionally invoke the static method SoundEffect.init() to pre-load all the sound files, so that the play is not paused while loading the file for the first time.
4. You can use the static variable SoundEffect.volume to mute the sound.

Author:
Erik Miller, Jay Sathe, Tristan Seroff, Christian Ciabatoni
